.TH "fsl_upm_run_pattern" 9 "fsl_upm_run_pattern" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_upm_run_pattern \- actually run an UPM pattern
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_upm_run_pattern
.BI "(struct fsl_upm *upm "  ","
.BI "void __iomem *io_base "  ","
.BI "u32 mar "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "upm" 12
pointer to the fsl_upm structure obtained via fsl_upm_find
.IP "io_base" 12
remapped pointer to where memory access should happen
.IP "mar" 12
MAR register content during pattern execution
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function triggers dummy write to the memory specified by the io_base,
thus UPM pattern actually executed. Note that mar usage depends on the
pre-programmed AMX bits in the UPM RAM.
